title: President Donald J. Trump Announces Presidential Delegation to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Laurentino Cortizo of Panama – The White House
content:
Statements & Releases			
Issued on:
June 26, 2019
Today, President Donald J. Trump announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Panama City, Panama, to attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Laurentino Cortizo on July 1, 2019.The Honorable Wilbur Ross, Secretary of Commerce, will lead the delegation.Members of the Presidential Delegation:Mr. T. Ulrich Brechbühl, Counselor of the Department, U.S. Department of StateMs. Roxanne Cabral, Chargé d’Affaires, U.S. Embassy PanamaThe Honorable Marshall Billingslea, Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for Terrorist Financing, U.S. Department of the TreasuryThe Honorable Mauricio Claver-Carone, Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for Western Hemisphere Affairs, National Security CouncilMrs. Julie Chung, Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs, U.S. Department of StateMr. Tim Smucker, Member, Advisory Council for Trade Policy Negotiations; Chairman Emeritus, The J.M. Smucker CompanyMr. Jay Collins, Jr., Vice Chairman of Banking, Capital Markets & Advisory, Citigroup
